com.cyc.kb.client

Class KbObjectImpl<T extends CycObject>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cyc.kb.client.KbObjectImpl<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - type of CycObject core
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.cyc.kb.KbObject
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AssertionImpl, KbTermImpl, SentenceImpl, SymbolImpl, VariableImpl

    public class KbObjectImpl<T extends CycObject>
extends Object
implements com.cyc.kb.KbObject
    The base class for all the other classes in this package. Each KBObject is basically a facade for an object in the Cyc KB, and as such it provides common methods to make, retrieve, and remove CycL Assertions.

    • Method Detail

      • convertKBObjectToCycObject

        public static Object convertKBObjectToCycObject(Object arg)
        Attempts to return a CycObject (or a Java primitive object) based on the KBObject (or a Java primitive object). A CycObject or a subclass of it, is the primary representation of the BaseClient. It represents the same concept in the KB as the KBObject. The CycObject is useful when the user has to do something the KB API does not support.
        Parameters:
        arg - the inputs KBObject that will be converted to a CycObject
        Returns:
        the CycObject representation of the input ARG

      • checkAndCastObject

        public static <T> T checkAndCastObject(Object o)
                                throws com.cyc.kb.exception.CreateException
        Attempts to return an Object (expected to be of type T) for the input Object o. For basic Java objects like String, Number and Date, the object is returned without any modification. CycObjects are converted to KBObjects, of the most specific type possible.
        Type Parameters:

        Parameters:

      • get

        public static com.cyc.kb.KbObject get(CycObject cycObject)
                               throws com.cyc.kb.exception.CreateException,
                                      com.cyc.kb.exception.KbTypeException
        Get the KBObject that corresponds to cycObject. Throws exceptions if the object isn't in the KB. This is a very general factory method to build a KBObject from any arbitrary CycObject without any kind of semantic check on the CycObject. This is used as a "catch all" in the API, but otherwise it should never be used.
        Parameters:
        cycObject - the underlying CycObject to be wrapped
        Returns:
        the KBObject wrapping the cycObject.
        Throws:
        com.cyc.kb.exception.CreateException
        com.cyc.kb.exception.KbTypeException

      • getRestriction

        public com.cyc.kb.Sentence getRestriction()
        This method returns a getSentenceService with the type restriction of the KbObject or its subclasses, even the ones extended outside of KB API. For example, the restriction for a KbPredicate object would be (isa <THIS PRED> #$Predicate). This is most useful for building sentences of KB Object typed-variables, for use in rules and queries.
        Returns:
        the restriction getSentenceService for the class

      • isValidCore

        protected boolean isValidCore(CycObject cycObject)
                       throws com.cyc.kb.exception.KbRuntimeException,
                              com.cyc.kb.exception.KbServerSideException
        This not part of the public, supported KB API. Check that the candidate core object is valid for this type. This is part of the bootstrapping process, where we check the core before we build a KB Object. At this point, we can not use any KB API methods or getCore(). This checks the validity of only KBTerm subclasses. The core validity for Assertion and its subclasses, Sentence, Variable and Symbol are handled by the individual classes If a Variable is wrapped by any subclass of KBTerm, then it is always considered valid core. This is to allow representing a #$CycLDenotationalTerm and #$CycLVariable of a given type (#$Collection) using same KBTerm subclass.
        Parameters:
        cycObject - the object that is checked for type given by getTypeString()
        Returns:
        if a cycObject is of a given type
        Throws:
        com.cyc.kb.exception.KbRuntimeException - if there is a problem connecting to Cyc
        com.cyc.kb.exception.KbServerSideException - if there is problem executing a SubL command NOTE: This does not throw KBTypeException just because there is a server error.
